From: starseeker <starseeker@users.noreply.github.com>
Subject: [PATCH] Fix USE_MGL_NAMESPACE GetProcAddress lookup and glprocs.h OpenGL 1.3 core function entries

When OSMesa is built with USE_MGL_NAMESPACE (the default), all exported GL
symbols are renamed from "glFoo" to "mglFoo" to allow OSMesa and a system
OpenGL implementation to coexist in the same process.

Two related bugs prevent OSMesaGetProcAddress from resolving the OpenGL 1.3
core multitexture functions (glActiveTexture, glMultiTexCoord*) by their
mangled mgl-prefixed names:

Bug 1 – glapi.c: _glapi_get_proc_address does not handle mgl-prefixed names
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
The original _glapi_get_proc_address() returns NULL for any name that does
not begin with "gl". Under USE_MGL_NAMESPACE callers pass "mglFoo" names,
which fail this guard immediately.

Additionally, the static dispatch table (glprocs.h) stores function names
WITHOUT the "mgl" prefix (e.g. "glActiveTexture"), so even if the guard were
relaxed, a direct lookup of "mglActiveTexture" in find_entry() would find no
match because the stored key is "glActiveTexture".

Fix: extend _glapi_get_proc_address to accept "mgl"-prefixed names and, after
a direct static-table lookup fails, fall back to stripping the leading "m" and
retrying with the "gl"-prefixed name.

--- a/src/glapi/glapi.c
+++ b/src/glapi/glapi.c
@@ -667,8 +667,26 @@ _glapi_get_proc_address(const char *funcName)
     struct _glapi_function * entry;
     GLuint i;
 
-    if (funcName[0] != 'g' || funcName[1] != 'l')
-	return NULL;
+#ifdef USE_MGL_NAMESPACE
+    /* With name mangling, accept both "mgl" and "gl" prefixed names */
+    if (funcName[0] == 'm' && funcName[1] == 'g' && funcName[2] == 'l') {
+        /* mgl prefixed name - this is the expected case */
+    } else if (funcName[0] == 'g' && funcName[1] == 'l') {
+        /* gl prefixed name - we'll handle this below */
+    } else {
+        return NULL;
+    }
+#else
+    if (funcName[0] != 'g' || funcName[1] != 'l')
+        return NULL;
+#endif
 
     /* search extension functions first */
     for (i = 0; i < NumExtEntryPoints; i++) {
@@ -686,6 +704,21 @@ _glapi_get_proc_address(const char *funcName)
 	    return func;
     }
 
+#ifdef USE_MGL_NAMESPACE
+    /* If we're using name mangling, try alternative name lookups.
+     * The static table stores "glFoo" keys but the Address field holds
+     * "mglFoo" pointers; a lookup of "mglFoo" therefore misses on the
+     * first pass above, so retry by stripping the leading "m". */
+    if (funcName[0] == 'm' && funcName[1] == 'g' && funcName[2] == 'l') {
+        const char *unmangledName = funcName + 1; /* "mglFoo" -> "glFoo" */
+        const _glapi_proc func = get_static_proc_address(unmangledName);
+        if (func)
+            return func;
+    }
+#endif
+
     entry = add_function_name(funcName);
     return (entry == NULL) ? NULL : entry->dispatch_stub;
 }


Bug 2 – glprocs.h: OpenGL 1.3 core alias entries use wrong function name
------------------------------------------------------------------------
The static_functions[] table has two entries for each multitexture function:
  - an ARB extension entry  (offset ~5000s): "glActiveTextureARB" -> mglActiveTextureARB
  - an OpenGL 1.3 core entry (offset ~14000s): "glActiveTexture"   -> ???

In the original file the core entries (second block, offsets 14879 onward)
incorrectly use the ARB function pointer even though the string table at
those offsets holds the non-ARB names:

  NAME_FUNC_OFFSET(14879, glActiveTextureARB, _gloffset_ActiveTextureARB),
                   ^^^^^^ should be glActiveTexture

With USE_MGL_NAMESPACE the macro expands to:
  { 14879, (_glapi_proc) mglActiveTextureARB, _gloffset_ActiveTextureARB }

So OSMesaGetProcAddress("mglActiveTexture"):
  1. Direct lookup of "mglActiveTexture" fails (table stores "glActiveTexture")
  2. Fallback lookup of "glActiveTexture" succeeds, but returns mglActiveTextureARB
     instead of mglActiveTexture.

While mglActiveTexture and mglActiveTextureARB both dispatch to the same
underlying _mesa_ActiveTextureARB, returning the wrong function pointer is
incorrect: callers that compare the returned pointer to the symbol address of
mglActiveTexture (as Obol/Coin does in SoGLContext_instance via cc_dl_sym)
will see a mismatch and may disable the extension.

Fix: use the non-ARB function name for the 34 OpenGL 1.3 core alias entries
so that the Address field correctly holds mglActiveTexture (etc.) instead of
mglActiveTextureARB.

--- a/src/glapi/glprocs.h
+++ b/src/glapi/glprocs.h
@@ -1966,40 +1966,40 @@ static const glprocs_table_t static_functions[] = {
     NAME_FUNC_OFFSET(14821, glTexImage3D, _gloffset_TexImage3D),
     NAME_FUNC_OFFSET(14837, glTexSubImage3D, _gloffset_TexSubImage3D),
