Notes
-----
- Both mglActiveTexture and mglActiveTextureARB ultimately dispatch to the same
  underlying _mesa_ActiveTextureARB function, so both bugs are latent: the
  function works but the wrong symbol address is returned by GetProcAddress.

- The dispatch-offset field (_gloffset_ActiveTextureARB) is unchanged: the
  OpenGL 1.3 core function shares the same dispatch slot as the ARB extension,
  so the third argument is intentionally kept as the ARB offset constant.

- The NAME_FUNC_OFFSET macro under USE_MGL_NAMESPACE expands to:
    { Name_offset, (_glapi_proc) mgl##FuncName, Offset }
  so changing the function name field from "glActiveTextureARB" to
  "glActiveTexture" changes the stored address from mglActiveTextureARB to
  mglActiveTexture. The corresponding function symbols are defined in
  src/main/dispatch.c (via glapitemp.h) under both names.

Tested-with: obol/Coin scene-graph library using OBOL_OSMESA_BUILD;
  render_bump_map, render_multi_texture, render_environment, render_texture3
  and render_cubemap all produce correct pixel output after this fix.
